  "info": {
    "name": "todo-app API Reference",
    "description": "Complete API reference for the TODO application built with Node.js and Express.\n\n## Overview\nThis is a RESTful API for managing TODO items with full CRUD operations. The API uses an in-memory data store and returns JSON responses.\n\n## Base URL\n`http://localhost:3000`\n\n## Response Format\nAll responses follow a consistent format:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true/false,\n  \"data\": {...},\n  \"error\": \"error message\" // only present on errors\n}\n```\n\n## TODO Object Structure\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"title\": \"Task title\",\n  \"description\": \"Task description\",\n  \"completed\": false,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n- 400: Bad Request (validation errors)\n- 404: Not Found (TODO doesn't exist)\n- 500: Internal Server Error",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
